{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:psalms.83",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 83,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 83 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:1",
      "text": "God, don’t keep silent. Don’t keep silent, and don’t be still, God.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:2",
      "text": "For, behold, your enemies are stirred up. Those who hate you have lifted up their heads.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:3",
      "text": "They conspire with cunning against your people. They plot against your cherished ones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:4",
      "text": "“Come,” they say, “let’s destroy them as a nation, that the name of Israel may be remembered no more.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:5",
      "text": "For they have conspired together with one mind. They form an alliance against you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:6",
      "text": "The tents of Edom and the Ishmaelites; Moab, and the Hagrites;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:7",
      "text": "Gebal, Ammon, and Amalek; Philistia with the inhabitants of Tyre;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:8",
      "text": "Assyria also is joined with them. They have helped the children of Lot. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:9",
      "text": "Do to them as you did to Midian, as to Sisera, as to Jabin, at the river Kishon;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:10",
      "text": "who perished at Endor, who became as dung for the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:11",
      "text": "Make their nobles like Oreb and Zeeb, yes, all their princes like Zebah and Zalmunna,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:12",
      "text": "who said, “Let’s take possession of God’s pasture lands.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:13",
      "text": "My God, make them like tumbleweed, like chaff before the wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:14",
      "text": "As the fire that burns the forest, as the flame that sets the mountains on fire,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:15",
      "text": "so pursue them with your tempest, and terrify them with your storm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:16",
      "text": "Fill their faces with confusion, that they may seek your name, Yahweh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:17",
      "text": "Let them be disappointed and dismayed forever. Yes, let them be confounded and perish;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.83.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 83,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 83:18",
      "text": "that they may know that you alone, whose name is Yahweh, are the Most High over all the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
